.TH _SIMPLE SHELL "05 May 2024" "1.0" "simple shell page"

.SH NAME
hsh Simple Shell \-  command language interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Interactive mode
.TP
.B ./hsh
.TP
$ <command> <flag1> <flag2> …
.TP
$ ls
.TP
$ ls -lan
.TP
$ mkdir hello
.TP
.B Non-interactive mode
.TP
Command | ./hsh
.TP
echo “/bin/ls” | ./hsh
.TP
echo “ls -l” | ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
`hsh` is a simple custom shell implementation that allows users to execute commands and interact with the system. It provides a basic command-line interface for users to input commands and receive responses from the program.
.SH COMMANDS
.B exit:
- Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env:
- Displays the system environment variables.
.TP
.B Clear
- Clean the terminal screen
.SH Commands
.B Absolute path
.TP
This shell executes commands given in the form of an absolute path:
.TP
.B Input
.TP
$ /bin/ls -l
.TP
.B Output
.TP
total 72
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root  1230 May  8 11:31 executeCommand.c
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 17064 May  8 11:19 hsh
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   171 May  8 09:35 AUTHORS
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root  1265 May  8 11:31 main.c
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   303 May  8 11:31 main.h
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root  2324 May  8 09:48 man_1_simple_shell
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   502 May  8 11:31 path.c
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   208 May  8 11:31 printEnv.c
.TP
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root  2049 May  8 09:35 README.md
.SH USAGE
To compile and run the custom shell on your system, follow these steps:
.TP
1. Clone the repository:
.TP
git clone https://github.com/sayka88/holbertonschool-simple_shell.git
.TP
cd holbertonschool-simple_shell
.TP
2. Compile the source code using GCC:
.TP
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.TP
3. Run the shell:
.TP
./hsh
.TP
Once the shell is running, you can interact with it using the command-line interface. Here are some commands you can try:
.TP
- Entering commands: Type in various commands and press Enter to execute them.
.TP
- Exiting the shell: Use the "exit" command to exit the shell.
.TP
- Displaying environment variables: Use the "env" command to print the system environment variables.I
